
<div class="hero-unit">
  <h1>Set up Password-less Logins with your PGP Key</h1>
</div>

<div class="container">

  <div class="section">

    <h2>PGP Key Setup Instructions</h2>

    <p>You can sign in on indieauth.com without relying on any external providers by signing a challenge with your PGP key.</p>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <h3>1. Link to your PGP key on your home page</h3>

        <p>On your home page, link to one or more PGP keys and add the <code>rel="pgpkey"</code> attribute to the links.</p>
        <p>This may look something like the following:
        <pre><%== '<link rel="pgpkey" href="/key.pub">' %></pre>
      </div><!-- span -->
    </div><!-- row -->

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <h3>2. Sign in on indieauth.com</h3>

        <p>Make sure to click "re-scan" if you've previously signed in before and have just added your key.</p>

        <p>When you sign in, you'll see a PGP option listed! Clicking it will present a challenge that you will need to sign with your private key.</p>

        <p><img src="/img/gpg-plaintext.png" width="380" class="thumbnail"></p>

        <p>Sign the text and replace it with the signed version.</p>

        <h4>GPG Tools</h4>
        <p>If you have <a href="https://gpgtools.org/">GPG Tools</a> for OS X installed, you can use the "Services" menu to quickly sign the text.</p>
        <p><img src="/img/gpg-services-sign.png" class="thumbnail"></p>

        <h4>GnuPG</h4>
        <p>If you use gpg from the command line you can sign a text message with the following command.</p>
        <pre>$ echo '(challenge from indieauth.com)' | gpg --clearsign --armor </pre>

        <h4>Keybase.io</h4>
        <p>If you are using <a href="https://keybase.io">Keybase.io</a> you can sign it on the command line with <code>keybase sign -m 'challenge text from indieauth.com'</code></p>

      </div><!-- span -->
    </div><!-- row -->

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <h3>3. Submit the signed text</h3>

        <p>Paste the signed text in the form field and click "Verify".</p>
        <p><img src="/img/gpg-signed.png" width="380" class="thumbnail"></p>
        <p>After the server verifies the signature matches that of your public key you chose, you will be signed in!</p>

      </div>
    </div>


  </div><!-- section -->

</div><!-- container -->

